race.comment: SA's premier stables are represented here with some well-bred youngsters. One of them is I AM OLE (3) for the powerful Richard and Chantelle Jolly stable. He's started single figures at both runs and has been only fair. This looks the easiest race he's contested and, with the benefit of race experience and a claim, he will be hard to beat here. JURA VAUDOIS (6) has placed in six of her 16 starts and, while she's had her chance, she's shown obvious ability and is bound to win one of these soon. She's got good early speed so she will make her own luck and take some catching. She can win if she doesn't get too much pressure. SIMPLY SID (2) has put in two career-best runs over this track and distance at his last two starts. He's drawn sticky here but he's an obvious top-three chance. Others to consider are MALDIVICA (10) and first-starter DIRTY OLD TOWN (8).
